channel.title: Out of these bands which one do you like the most?
channel.description:
I personally listen to every band here (and more) except My Chemical Romance. I currently Have 1,428 Songs = 103Hrs = 6.45GB of music.
These are the bands i listen to: (just because I have more albums then another doesn't mean I like that band more)
AC/DC - 4 Albums Aerosmith - 3 Albums Anthrax - 2 Albums Bad Acid Trip - 1 Album Billy Thorpe And The Aztecs - 1 Album Black Sabbath - 2 albums Cold Chisel - 1 Album Combichrist - 1 Album + 2 songs Deep Purple - 2 Albums Disturbed - 1 Album Drowning Pool - 2 Albums Gorillaz - 1 Album Greenday - 2 Albums Grand Theft Auto: Vice city sound track - 7 Albums Hatebreed - 1 Album Hilltop Hoods - 1 Album Iron Maiden - 3 Albums + 12 Songs Korn - 7 Albums + 4 Songs Lamb Of God - 1 Album Led Zeppelin - 2 Albums Limp Bizkit - 1 Album + 5 Songs Megadeth - 4 Albums + 10 Songs Metallica - 6 Albums + 16 Songs Motorhead - 2 Albums Midnight Oil - 5 Albums The Misfits - 2 Albums Mudvayne - 4 Albums Nickelback - 1 Album Nine Inch Nails - 2 Albums Nightiwish - 1 Album Opeth - 2 Albums Pantera - 3 Albums + 5 Songs Pink Floyd - 4 Albums Rodney Rude - 1 Album Saw I OST Saw II OST Saw III OST Slayer - 4 Albums + 16 Songs Slipknot - 1 Album + 17 Songs System Of A Down - 5 Albums The Cat Empire - 1 Album The Doors - 2 Albums George Thorogood - 1 Album The Living End - 1 Album The Rolling Stones - 3 Albums The Who - 1 Album Tokyo Drift OST Yes - 1 Album
I have been collecting music for a while (Just songs off limewire). But I started downloading whole albums from various sources. As soon as I started with albums my music collection grew largely. The places I have gotten my music from are: http://Albumbase.com Torrents (http://Demonoid.com) I downloaded some discographies. http://www.pen.eiu.edu/~acberger/Stuff/My_Music/ Frostwire (Same network as limewire) Http://ProjectW.org/
[b]NOTE: I reset all the votes at this time. And I updated the thread.[/b]
PS: I am always looking for good bands to listen to. As you can see I like metal mostly. And I am always looking for some more 70-80's Metal bands.
